  "id": "TEMA-VIDYA-Strategy-001",
  "name": "TEMA-VIDYA Trend Following Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm utilizes a combination of the Triple Exponential Moving Average (TEMA) and the Variable Index Dynamic Average (VIDYA) to identify trend-following opportunities. It generates long signals when TEMA(20) crosses above VIDYA(14) with sufficient volume, and short signals when the opposite occurs.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level TrendFollowing trading algorithm in Pine Script that uses a combination of Triple Exponential Moving Average (TEMA) set to 20 periods and the Variable Index Dynamic Average (VIDYA) set to 14 periods on the 1-hour timeframe. Entry condition: go long when TEMA(20) crosses above VIDYA(14) and volume is above its 20-period moving average; go short when TEMA(20) crosses below VIDYA(14) and volume is below its 20-period moving average. Exit condition: close positions when the price closes outside the Keltner Channels calculated on 20 periods with an Average True Range (ATR) multiplier of 1.5, signaling trend exhaustion. Include strict stop-loss at 1.5 ATR and trailing stop based on 0.75 ATR. Implement appropriate signals to optimize entries and exits respecting volatility and volume filters only.",
